-- [MN] Source: Official Publication of the State of Minnesota, Revisor of Statutes (revisor.mn.gov), Minnesota Statutes 2025. All quotes verified against the official PDF text of each section.
-- [MN] RESIDENTIAL ACT (Chapter 504B): residential-only. 504B.001 subd. 12 defines "residential tenant" as a person occupying a dwelling in a residential building under a lease; 504B.001 subd. 11 defines "residential building" to include single-family homes and multiple-family units such as apartments. Chapter 504B does NOT govern commercial tenancies. 504B.211 subd. 7 explicitly exempts manufactured home parks from the privacy/entry section (those are governed by ch. 327C).
-- [MN] OMITTED residential provisions (statute does NOT specify a value — not invented):
-- [MN] - deposit_max_months: Minnesota has NO statutory cap on security deposit amount. 504B.178 governs interest (1%/yr) and return but contains no maximum-deposit limit.
-- [MN] - late_fee_grace_days: 504B.177 imposes no mandatory grace period. It requires a written agreement that "must specify when the late fee will be imposed," but sets no statutory minimum number of days before a late fee may apply. No number exists to report.
-- [MN] - notice_to_vacate_days: 504B.135 does NOT state a fixed day count. The notice "must be at least as long as the interval between the time rent is due or three months, whichever is less." It is interval-based (one rental period for a typical month-to-month tenancy), not a fixed statutory number of days, so no numeric value is reported.
-- [MN] UNIT-TYPE / ACT NOTES:
-- [MN] - mobile_home: Chapter 327C (Manufactured Home Park Lot Rentals) is the dedicated landlord-tenant act for mobile/manufactured home park LOT rentals. Key sections include 327C.015 (definitions), 327C.095 (park closings/conversions — 12-month notice). 327C.015 subd. 8 defines "manufactured home park" by reference to 327.14 subd. 3 and EXCLUDES facilities open three or fewer seasons per year, confirming a year-round-residency focus.
-- [MN] - rv_spot: Minnesota has NO dedicated landlord-tenant RENTAL-AGREEMENT act for recreational vehicle / camping space tenancies. Chapter 327 secs. 327.14-327.28 ('recreational camping area' = area used on a daily/nightly/weekly or longer basis for 5+ tents or recreational camping vehicles) is a Department of Health LICENSING / health / safety / sanitation regime, NOT a landlord-tenant act. It does not set entry notice, deposit, late-fee, or notice-to-vacate rules. Long-term RV-space rentals fall outside 327C (keyed to 'manufactured home') and outside 504B's manufactured-home-park exemption analysis; absent a specific RV rental statute, such tenancies default to general contract/common law. Listed here only to map the unit type to the closest on-point chapter.
-- [MN] - commercial: No commercial-specific landlord-tenant act exists in Minnesota statutes; commercial tenancies are governed by the lease contract and common law (504B is residential-only). Not included as a separate act to avoid inventing one.
-- [MN] - storage: No self-storage / self-service-storage landlord-tenant act was identified in the landlord-tenant title; not reported as a distinct act.
--
-- [SC] RESIDENTIAL ACT (Title 27, Ch. 40): "Dwelling unit" is defined to include landlord-owned mobile homes, so the residential act covers apartments, single-family dwellings, and landlord-owned mobile homes. Per § 27-40-120 the act excludes hotels/motels (transient occupancy), institutional residences, owner-occupied sale contracts, employment-conditioned housing, condominium/cooperative units occupied by the owner, agricultural premises, vacation time-shares, and emergency shelters.
-- [SC] PROVISIONS OMITTED (statute specifies NO value — not invented):
-- [SC] - deposit_max_months: OMITTED. Ch. 40 § 27-40-410 contains no cap on the security deposit amount. South Carolina does not limit deposit size by statute.
-- [SC] - late_fee_max_pct: OMITTED. Ch. 40 has no late-fee percentage cap. The only reference is § 27-40-210(11), which merely defines "rent" to include "late charges" without any limit.
-- [SC] - late_fee_grace_days: OMITTED. Ch. 40 requires no minimum grace period before a late fee may be charged.
-- [SC] Verified provisions present: entry notice (24 hrs, § 27-40-530), deposit return (30 days, § 27-40-410), month-to-month termination (30 days, § 27-40-770; week-to-week is 7 days under the same section).
-- [SC] OTHER ACTS:
-- [SC] - Manufactured Home Park Tenancy Act (Title 27, Ch. 47) governs manufactured home PARK LOTS (5+ lots offered for rent). It EXPLICITLY EXCLUDES recreational vehicles: § 27-47-120 excludes spaces "offered for occupancy by a vehicle which primarily is designed as temporary living quarters for recreational camping or travel use." Ch. 40 provisions apply to park tenancies where not inconsistent with Ch. 47.
-- [SC] - RV_SPOT: South Carolina has NO dedicated RV/recreational-vehicle long-term tenancy act. RVs are expressly excluded from Ch. 47, and RV-lot tenancies fall under general contract/lease law (and potentially Ch. 40 only if the RV qualifies as a "dwelling unit," which is fact-specific). No act was mapped to rv_spot.
-- [SC] - COMMERCIAL: South Carolina has NO dedicated commercial landlord-tenant act. Commercial tenancies are governed by general real-property and contract/common law within Title 27 (e.g., Ch. 35 ejectment of tenants, Ch. 37 landlord liens). No single statute maps cleanly to "commercial," so it was not listed as a discrete act.
-- [SC] - Self-Service Storage Facility Act (Title 39, Ch. 20) governs storage units; § 39-20 prohibits residential use of storage facilities and is a lien/commerce statute, not a residential landlord-tenant act.
-- [SC] SOURCING: All values verified against the official South Carolina Legislature site (scstatehouse.gov). Justia mirror (law.justia.com) returned HTTP 403 and was not relied upon for quotes; all evidence quotes are from the scstatehouse.gov chapter text.
