-- [UT] RESIDENTIAL ACT = Utah Fit Premises Act (Title 57 Ch. 22), paired with Residential Renters' Deposits (Title 57 Ch. 17) for deposit handling. "Residential rental unit" (57-22-2(5)) = renter's principal place of residence; expressly EXCLUDES mobile home lots and recreational property rented on an occasional basis — so apartment + single_family only.
-- [UT] UNIT-TYPE COVERAGE:
-- [UT] - apartment / single_family: Fit Premises Act + Renters' Deposits.
-- [UT] - mobile_home + rv_spot: Mobile Home Park Residency Act (Title 57 Ch. 16). 57-16-2 defines "fees" to include "charges for storage of recreational vehicles," and 78B-6-802(3) routes owner-resident-of-a-mobile-home unlawful detainer to Ch. 16. Utah has NO standalone RV-park residency act, so long-term RV spaces fall under the mobile-home park framework where applicable.
-- [UT] - commercial / storage: NO Utah-specific tenancy act. Governed by general contract law and the Title 78B-6 (Forcible Entry & Detainer) eviction code only. Not represented as an "act" above because no dedicated chapter exists.
-- [UT] PROVISIONS DELIBERATELY OMITTED (statute specifies NO value — not invented):
-- [UT] - deposit_max_months: Utah caps NO security-deposit amount. Title 57 Ch. 17 and Ch. 22 are silent on any maximum. OMITTED.
-- [UT] - late_fee_grace_days: Utah statute mandates NO grace period before a late fee may apply. 57-22-4(5) caps the late-fee AMOUNT (greater of 10% of rent or $75) but sets no minimum days-late trigger; grace, if any, is purely contractual. OMITTED.
-- [UT] CITATION SOURCING CAVEAT on notice_to_vacate_days: The 15-day month-to-month termination rule is NOT in the Fit Premises Act itself — it lives in the eviction code, Utah Code § 78B-6-802 (Title 78B, Judicial Code), which is the operative residential month-to-month termination statute. I cited 78B-6-802 directly and used its official le.utah.gov URL. The 5/6/2026-effective version (Amended by Chapter 401, 2026 General Session) was confirmed in force as of today and retains the 15-calendar-day figure (the prior 8/31/2020 version had identical language).
-- [UT] AMENDMENT/VERSION NOTES for annual-refresh discipline:
-- [UT] - 57-17-3 last amended Chapter 275, 2025 General Session (30-day return retained; the failure-to-comply cure window in 57-17-3(5) is 5 business days, $100 penalty under 57-17-5).
-- [UT] - 57-22-4 (entry + late fee + disclosure) last amended Chapter 98, 2021 General Session.
-- [UT] - 57-22-5 has a successor version "Effective 1/1/2027" (Chapter 445, 2026 General Session) but it concerns crime-victim/DV lock & termination rights, NOT entry/late-fee/deposit — no impact on the provisions above.
-- [UT] - 78B-6-802 superseded 5/6/2026; current version cited. URLs to the canonical (undated) le.utah.gov HTML pages are used for the act listings; PDF (versioned) URLs are used as sourceUrl for provisions because the HTML pages render statute text via JavaScript and return empty when fetched.
--

